<subSubSection id="F189654AFFA06B3AAF452449FE574B0D" pageId="20" pageNumber="501" type="description">
<paragraph id="B92C36C1FFA06B3AAF452449FF1D4D2F" blockId="20.[79,1035,375,1101]" pageId="20" pageNumber="501">
<emphasis id="8BE7EAD3FFA06B3AAF452449FF5B4ECF" box="[120,253,376,399]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="501">Description.</emphasis>
Cell outline elongate ovate, 20 Mm long and about 8±11 Mm wide, ¯attened, with squirming movement and with pellicular striations following a S-helix. Two emergent ¯agella are similar in width. The anterior ¯agellum is approximately 2±2.5 times the length of the cell and is longer than the posterior ¯agellum which is slightly longer than the cell. The ingestion organelle may be di cult to see. The reservoir is in the left ventral side of the cell and the nucleus is in the posterior part of the cell. Refractile bodies lie under the cell surface. Cells move by gliding. Rarely observed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B92C36C1FFA06B3AAF452746FE574B0D" blockId="20.[79,1035,375,1101]" pageId="20" pageNumber="501">
<emphasis id="8BE7EAD3FFA06B3AAF452746FF444DCF" box="[120,226,631,655]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="501">Remarks.</emphasis>
Previous reported cell lengths range from 17 to 39 Mm (
<bibRefCitation id="DD024B30FFA06B3AAC592746FF254DEF" author="LEMMERMANN, E." pageId="20" pageNumber="501" pagination="174" refId="ref41582" refString="LEMMERMANN, E., 1913, Chrysomonadinae, Cryptomonadinae, Eugleninae, Chloromonadinae und Gefarbte Flagellaten Unsicherer Stellung, in A. Pascher (ed.) Die SuEsswasserora Deutschlands, OEsterreich und der Schweiz, II (Jena: Fischer Verlag), pp. 115 ± 174." type="journal article" year="1913">Lemmermann, 1913</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="DD024B30FFA06B3AAFAE27A6FEA94DEF" author="STEIN, F. R." box="[147,271,663,687]" pageId="20" pageNumber="501" refId="ref43321" refString="STEIN, F. R., 1878, Der Organismus der Infusionsthiere. III. Der Organismus der Flagellaten I (Leipzig: Wilhelm Engelmann), 154 pp." type="book" year="1878">Stein, 1878</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="DD024B30FFA06B3AAE2227A6FD854DEF" author="HUBER-PESTALOZZI, G." box="[287,547,663,687]" pageId="20" pageNumber="501" refId="ref40973" refString="HUBER-PESTALOZZI, G., 1955, Das Phytoplankto n des SuEsswassers. 4. Euglenophyceen. (Stuttgart: Schweizerbartsche), 606 pp." type="book" year="1955">Huber-Pestalozzi, 1955</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="DD024B30FFA06B3AAD0E27A6FCCF4DEF" author="LARSEN, J. &amp; PATTERSON, D. J." box="[563,873,663,687]" pageId="20" pageNumber="501" pagination="937" refId="ref41333" refString="LARSEN, J. and PATTERSON, D. J., 1990, Some ¯ agellates (Protista) from tropical marine sediments, Journal of Natural History, 24, 801 ± 937." type="journal article" year="1990">Larsen and Patterson, 1990</bibRefCitation>
). This species was found in marine sites in 
<collectingCountry id="C1847651FFA06B3AAEAC2786FE724D8F" box="[401,468,695,719]" name="Brazil" pageId="20" pageNumber="501">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="C1847651FFA06B3AAD312786FD954D8F" box="[524,563,695,719]" name="Fiji" pageId="20" pageNumber="501">Fiji</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="DD024B30FFA06B3AAD782786FCDD4D8F" author="LARSEN, J. &amp; PATTERSON, D. J." box="[581,891,695,719]" pageId="20" pageNumber="501" pagination="937" refId="ref41333" refString="LARSEN, J. and PATTERSON, D. J., 1990, Some ¯ agellates (Protista) from tropical marine sediments, Journal of Natural History, 24, 801 ± 937." type="journal article" year="1990">Larsen and Patterson, 1990</bibRefCitation>
). Generally, our observations are in agreement with 
<bibRefCitation id="DD024B30FFA06B3AAD1F27E6FCD44DAE" author="LARSEN, J. &amp; PATTERSON, D. J." box="[546,882,726,750]" pageId="20" pageNumber="501" pagination="937" refId="ref41333" refString="LARSEN, J. and PATTERSON, D. J., 1990, Some ¯ agellates (Protista) from tropical marine sediments, Journal of Natural History, 24, 801 ± 937." type="journal article" year="1990">Larsen and Patterson (1990)</bibRefCitation>
. This species is distinguished by its elongate ovate shape. This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="7E934D42FFA06B3AAC4C27C6FF5B4C6E" authority="Dujardin, 1841" authorityName="Dujardin" authorityYear="1841" class="Euglenoidea" family="Peranemaceae" genus="Heteronema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Peranemida" pageId="20" pageNumber="501" phylum="Euglenozoa" rank="species" species="nebulosum">
<emphasis id="8BE7EAD3FFA06B3AAC4C27C6FBAD4C4E" box="[881,1035,758,782]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="501">H. nebulosum</emphasis>
Dujardin, 
<quantity id="7E6B9B24FFA06B3AAFF52627FF5B4C6E" box="[200,253,790,814]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.67614" pageId="20" pageNumber="501" unit="in" value="1841.0">1841</quantity>
</taxonomicName>
in general appearance, but 
<taxonomicName id="7E934D42FFA06B3AAD792626FD464C6E" authorityName="Dujardin" authorityYear="1841" box="[580,736,790,814]" class="Euglenoidea" family="Peranemaceae" genus="Heteronema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Peranemida" pageId="20" pageNumber="501" phylum="Euglenozoa" rank="species" species="nebulosum">
<emphasis id="8BE7EAD3FFA06B3AAD792626FD464C6E" box="[580,736,790,814]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="501">H. nebulosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is bigger and has a short recurrent ¯agellum. 
<taxonomicName id="7E934D42FFA06B3AAE082606FD604C0E" authority="Dujardin, 1841" authorityName="Dujardin" authorityYear="1841" box="[309,710,822,846]" class="Euglenoidea" family="Peranemaceae" genus="Peranema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Peranemida" pageId="20" pageNumber="501" phylum="Euglenozoa" rank="species" species="globulosa">
<emphasis id="8BE7EAD3FFA06B3AAE082606FDB44C0E" box="[309,530,822,846]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="501">Peranema globulosa</emphasis>
Dujardin, 1841
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="7E934D42FFA06B3AADC22606FBAC4C0E" authority="Skuja, 1948" authorityName="Skuja" authorityYear="1948" box="[767,1034,822,846]" class="Euglenoidea" family="Peranemaceae" genus="Heteronema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Peranemida" pageId="20" pageNumber="501" phylum="Euglenozoa" rank="species" species="sacculus">
<emphasis id="8BE7EAD3FFA06B3AADC22606FCD84C0E" box="[767,894,822,846]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="501">H. sacculus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="DD024B30FFA06B3AACBB2607FBAC4C0E" author="SKUJA, H." box="[902,1034,822,846]" pageId="20" pageNumber="501" pagination="399" refId="ref43143" refString="SKUJA, H., 1948, Taxonomie des Phytoplanktons einiger Seen in Uppland, Schweden, Symbolae Botanicae Upsalienses, 9, 5 ± 399." type="journal article" year="1948">Skuja, 1948</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
are synonyms of 
<taxonomicName id="7E934D42FFA06B3AAE122666FE4E4C2E" authorityName="Stein" authorityYear="1878" baseAuthorityName="Ehrenberg" baseAuthorityYear="1838" box="[303,488,854,878]" class="Euglenoidea" family="Peranemaceae" genus="Heteronema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Peranemida" pageId="20" pageNumber="501" phylum="Euglenozoa" rank="species" species="globuliferum">
<emphasis id="8BE7EAD3FFA06B3AAE122666FE4E4C2E" box="[303,488,854,878]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="501">H. globuliferum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="DD024B30FFA06B3AAD3C2667FD2F4C2E" author="STEIN, F. R." box="[513,649,854,878]" pageId="20" pageNumber="501" refId="ref43321" refString="STEIN, F. R., 1878, Der Organismus der Infusionsthiere. III. Der Organismus der Flagellaten I (Leipzig: Wilhelm Engelmann), 154 pp." type="book" year="1878">Stein, 1878</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="DD024B30FFA06B3AAD9E2666FC5E4C2E" author="LARSEN, J. &amp; PATTERSON, D. J." box="[675,1016,854,878]" pageId="20" pageNumber="501" pagination="937" refId="ref41333" refString="LARSEN, J. and PATTERSON, D. J., 1990, Some ¯ agellates (Protista) from tropical marine sediments, Journal of Natural History, 24, 801 ± 937." type="journal article" year="1990">Larsen and Patterson, 1990</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="7E934D42FFA06B3AAF722647FE524CCD" authority="Skuja, 1939" authorityName="Skuja" authorityYear="1939" box="[79,500,885,909]" class="Euglenoidea" family="Peranemaceae" genus="Heteronema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Peranemida" pageId="20" pageNumber="501" phylum="Euglenozoa" rank="species" species="abruptum">
<emphasis id="8BE7EAD3FFA06B3AAF722647FEF24CCD" box="[79,340,885,909]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="501">Heteronema abruptum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="DD024B30FFA06B3AAE582644FE524CCD" author="SKUJA, H." box="[357,500,885,909]" pageId="20" pageNumber="501" pagination="169" refId="ref43116" refString="SKUJA, H., 1939, Beitrag zur Algenora Lettlands II, Acta Horti botanici Universitatis latviensis, 11 ± 12, 41 ± 169." type="journal article" year="1939">Skuja, 1939</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
also appears to be a junior synonym of 
<emphasis id="8BE7EAD3FFA06B3AAF7226A7FEA14CED" box="[79,263,917,941]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="501">
<taxonomicName id="7E934D42FFA06B3AAF7226A7FF584CED" authorityName="Stein" authorityYear="1878" baseAuthorityName="Ehrenberg" baseAuthorityYear="1838" box="[79,254,917,941]" class="Euglenoidea" family="Peranemaceae" genus="Heteronema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Peranemida" pageId="20" pageNumber="501" phylum="Euglenozoa" rank="species" species="globuliferum">H. globuliferum</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Skuja described 
<taxonomicName id="7E934D42FFA06B3AAEF126A7FDFF4CED" authorityName="Skuja" authorityYear="1939" box="[460,601,917,941]" class="Euglenoidea" family="Peranemaceae" genus="Heteronema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Peranemida" pageId="20" pageNumber="501" phylum="Euglenozoa" rank="species" species="abruptum">
<emphasis id="8BE7EAD3FFA06B3AAEF126A7FDFF4CED" box="[460,601,917,941]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="501">H. abruptum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without reference to 
<taxonomicName id="7E934D42FFA06B3AAC6E26A7FBA54CED" authorityName="Stein" authorityYear="1878" baseAuthorityName="Ehrenberg" baseAuthorityYear="1838" box="[851,1027,917,941]" class="Euglenoidea" family="Peranemaceae" genus="Heteronema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Peranemida" pageId="20" pageNumber="501" phylum="Euglenozoa" rank="species" species="globuliferum">
<emphasis id="8BE7EAD3FFA06B3AAC6E26A7FBA54CED" box="[851,1027,917,941]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="501">H. globuliferum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="7E934D42FFA06B3AAF722687FEFC4C8D" authorityName="Skuja" authorityYear="1939" box="[79,346,949,973]" class="Euglenoidea" family="Peranemaceae" genus="Heteronema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Peranemida" pageId="20" pageNumber="501" phylum="Euglenozoa" rank="species" species="abruptum">
<emphasis id="8BE7EAD3FFA06B3AAF722687FEFC4C8D" box="[79,346,949,973]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="501">Heteronema abruptum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
measures 17±30 Mm which is within the range of 
<taxonomicName id="7E934D42FFA06B3AAF7226E7FF594CAD" authorityName="Stein" authorityYear="1878" baseAuthorityName="Ehrenberg" baseAuthorityYear="1838" box="[79,255,981,1005]" class="Euglenoidea" family="Peranemaceae" genus="Heteronema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Peranemida" pageId="20" pageNumber="501" phylum="Euglenozoa" rank="species" species="globuliferum">
<emphasis id="8BE7EAD3FFA06B3AAF7226E7FF594CAD" box="[79,255,981,1005]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="501">H. globuliferum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The anterior ¯agellum of 
<taxonomicName id="7E934D42FFA06B3AAD0F26E7FD184CAD" authorityName="Skuja" authorityYear="1939" box="[562,702,981,1005]" class="Euglenoidea" family="Peranemaceae" genus="Heteronema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Peranemida" pageId="20" pageNumber="501" phylum="Euglenozoa" rank="species" species="abruptum">
<emphasis id="8BE7EAD3FFA06B3AAD0F26E7FD184CAD" box="[562,702,981,1005]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="501">H. abruptum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is about twice the cell length and the posterior ¯agellum is about 1±1.5 times the cell length. There are minor diOEerences which we do not regard as signi®cant; they have slightly diOEerent shapes and 
<taxonomicName id="7E934D42FFA06B3AAFBE2107FEB74B0D" authorityName="Skuja" authorityYear="1939" box="[131,273,1077,1101]" class="Euglenoidea" family="Peranemaceae" genus="Heteronema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Peranemida" pageId="20" pageNumber="501" phylum="Euglenozoa" rank="species" species="abruptum">
<emphasis id="8BE7EAD3FFA06B3AAFBE2107FEB74B0D" box="[131,273,1077,1101]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="501">H. abruptum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is slightly broader.
